The paper proposes a novel approach for supervised classification of signals on a fixed graph, which involves the use of a Convolutional Cluster Pooling layer. This layer exploits multi-scale clustering to highlight locally connected regions on the input graph, and generalizes well-established neural models such as CNNs on irregular and complex domains. The paper presents extensive experiments on different datasets to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed technique. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural models, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
